# Devices: Xiaomi Redmi Note 8T
*A budget Android phone from like 2019 I think*

<br>

This was a really cool phone when I first got it. It was actually my dad's, but I switched my Honor 9X for it. I started using it in the start of 2020, and mained it on and off for the next 3 years
It was kinda slow, but I personally like MIUI.

<br>

The camera was fine, [here's an image shot on it](/photos/img_20211208_135414.jpg)


I decided to custom ROM it in the summer of 2022. I installed LineageOS 18 on it, which was quite nice. After that, I decided to install Pixel Experience, which was also nice,
but a bit laggy.

<br>

I tried to flash it to stock firmware again, but managed to brick it by installing Redmi Note 8's firmware (instead of the 8T's). I couldn't find a way to fix it, so I switched
back to my iPhone 6, and bought an iPhone XS on Christmas of 2022. 
In May of 2023, I decided to try to get it working again. I followed an XDA-thread on how to fix it, but unfortunately that was for the Redmi Note 8, and didn't work for my variant.
I did a bit of digging, and spent a few hours trying things, and I eventually got it to work


<details>
    <summary>TikTok made from old footage of me fixing it</summary>
    <video controls src="https://homecdn.frii.site/v0f044gc0000cir34g3c77u27knteh60.MP4" />
</details>

<br>

After fixing the phone, I mained it for a couple of weeks, before switching back to my iPhone XS. It worked fine I guess.
I started making "techtok" tiktoks in the summer of 2023, and made a couple of videos about this phone.

<details>
    <summary>Some old TikToks of mine which showcased the phone</summary>
    <video controls src="https://homecdn.frii.site/v0f044gc0000cj0ftqrc77ualmm0nrag.MP4" />

